The advisory committee shall advise the commissioner of state health services on:
(1) the storage and maintenance of epinephrine delivery systems and medication for respiratory distress on school campuses and campuses of institutions of higher education;
(2) the training of school personnel and school volunteers, and of personnel and volunteers at institutions of higher education, in the administration of an epinephrine delivery system;
(3) the training of school personnel and school volunteers, and of personnel and volunteers at institutions of higher education, in the administration of a medication for respiratory distress; and
(4) a plan for:
(A) one or more school personnel members or school volunteers trained in the administration of an epinephrine delivery system to be on each school campus;
(B) one or more school personnel members or school volunteers trained in the administration of medication for respiratory distress to be on each school campus;
(C) one or more personnel members or volunteers of an institution of higher education trained in the administration of an epinephrine delivery system to be on each campus of an institution of higher education; and
(D) one or more personnel members or volunteers of an institution of higher education trained in the administration of medication for respiratory distress to be on each campus of an institution of higher education.
